<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Containing WR — Silent W Scrabble Words</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">WR is the "silent W" digraph — WRITE, WRONG, WRAP all hide a 4-point W in plain sight. Like KN (silent K), WR gives you a premium consonant that scores big on the board while being invisible in speech. With only 2 W tiles in the bag, knowing your WR words ensures you never waste this valuable tile.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">WR Value Breakdown</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">W(4) + R(1) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">50+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid WR words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">WR-</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Always at start</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>W is worth 4 points — tied with F, H, V, and Y as the 6th most valuable tiles. Every WR word starts with a guaranteed 5-point foundation from just two tiles, and the remaining tiles often push scores to 10-14 points easily.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scoring WR Words</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
